pros:
Company provides Good Trainings and recaps of basic topics;
Daily Transportation benefits; Good vacation benefits;
Adequate support for learning in many projects;
Fixed working hours- you wont be asked to extend unless it is top priority;
Good place to learn corporate skills;

cons:
Major con is that company chooses your stream of technology while you enter through Mass recruit and it takes time to switch to preferred tech.
If you get stuck in micromanaged projects- work could be monotonous;
Many internal benefits or allowances varies team wise and Pay is set to minimum despite your efforts and work culture suffers because of it.
